quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  106,1,"(It is a great Grace and Protection from Allah), for the taming of the Quraish"
  106,2,"(And with all those Allah's Grace and Protections for their taming, We cause) the (Quraish) caravans to set forth safe in winter (to the south), and in summer (to the north without any fear)"
  106,3,So let them worship (Allah) the Lord of this House (the Ka'bah in Makkah)
  106,4,"(He) Who has fed them against hunger, and has made them safe from fear"
  107,1,Have you seen him who denies the Recompense
  107,2,That is he who repulses the orphan (harshly)
  107,3,And urges not the feeding of AlMiskin (the poor)
  107,4,So woe unto those performers of Salat (prayers) (hypocrites)
  107,5,Who delay their Salat (prayer) from their stated fixed times
  107,6,Those who do good deeds only to be seen (of men)
  107,7,"And refuse Al-Ma'un (small kindnesses e.g. salt, sugar, water, etc)"
  108,1,"Verily, We have granted you (O Muhammad (Peace be upon him)) Al-Kauthar (a river in Paradise)"
  108,2,Therefore turn in prayer to your Lord and sacrifice (to Him only)
  108,3,"For he who makes you angry (O Muhammad (Peace be upon him)), - he will be cut off (from every good thing in this world and in the Hereafter)"